<div class="py-6 px-8">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-8">
    <div class="form-field">
      <% if @company.premium? %>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <%= form.label :insights_webhook_url, 'Slack webhooks url', class: 'form-label' %>
          <%= form.text_field :insights_webhook_url, class: 'form-value full', placeholder: 'https://hooks.slack.com/services/TTTTTTTTTTT/BBBBBBBBBBB/G00000000000000000000000' %>
        </div>
        <div>
          <%= form.label :insights_discord_webhook_url, 'Discord webhooks url', class: 'form-label' %>
          <%= form.text_field :insights_discord_webhook_url, class: 'form-value full', placeholder: 'https://discord.com/api/webhooks/000111222333444555/long-key' %>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <p>This configuration is available for premium accounts.</p>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p>If this configuration enabled then you can set url of Slack and Discord webhook and notifications will be send there.</p>
      <p>For getting Slack webhook url you need to create Slack application and enabled incoming webhooks, all details you can find by url <a href="https://api.slack.com/messaging/webhooks">Slack incoming webhooks</a>.</p>
      <p>For getting Discord webhook url you need to change settings of any channel in Discord. After selecting channel settings visit Integration / Webhooks, create webhook and copy its url.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
